courses.learning_outcomes:
1. To appreciate various urban processes and the impact of urban development and redevelopment in the transformation of cities by studying existing urban districts in Hong Kong;
2. To learn to engage and communicate with multiple stakeholders and community members both remotely and in-person to understand local aspirations, key issues, community concerns;
3. To work in groups in planning, organizing or participating remotely in seminars, exhibitions and workshops to gaining hands on experience;
4. To assess the needs and aspirations of the community and various stakeholders including residents, users and visitors as well;
5. To understand current evolution of city design and community engagement in the planning process and the relevance of these to design development.
6. To become aware of the importance of urban design and community engagement processes in planning and development of cities and communities to come up with innovative and creative solutions that are smart and resilient while being socially responsive, environmentally sustainable and economically viable as an appropriate response to the unfolding any urban emergency; and
7. To consolidate their research, writing and presentation skills including written and oral communication skills.

Upon completing the studio, students will be able to:
- Understand the complex and multi-disciplinary nature of environmental design approaches at a range of urban planning scales;
- Understand the complex relationships between environmental, economic and social sustainability;
- Consider environmental and liveability considerations early into the design process, and be able to critically assess conceptual urban design proposals in relation to environmental performance aspects;
- Understand and address contemporary global concerns around urbanisation, climate change, human health and quality of life
- Apply improved academic research, analysis, writing and presentation skills, and be familiar with the relevant issues, concepts and terminologies related to sustainable urban design
